UIMA Summer School Tutorial and Presentation Details UIMA 101 : The new UIMA tutorial
Tuesday August 26 9 : 00AM - 4 : 30PM in GN-K35
UIMA 101 is a hands-on programming tutorial .

The advanced topics tutorial is designed for people who have some experience with UIMA and want to use new capabilities of UIMA 1.0 to address one or more of the following
Advanced Topics
:
1 ) Collection Processing and Collection Processing Engines ( CPEs ) 2 ) Multi-Threading and CAS Pooling
3 ) Using the UIMA adapter framework to integrate network TAEs with Java TAEs
4 ) A Semantic Search Application that brings it all together
Prerequisites for UIMA 201 1 ) UIMA 101 Tutorial OR Extensive UIMA Experience
